<div type="definition">
<p>BASIC NATURE so as to TEND to SPEAK EXCESSIVELY OFTEN AND for an EXCESSIVELY LONG TIME.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. There is no current word for this notion in pre-Buddhist Chinese. Tà 誻 "talkative" is the only word that comes to mind, and this is a very rare word.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>愛說話 is current modern mild way of complaining of talkativeness.</p>
<p>拉不斷扯不斷 makes a stronger complaint.</p>
<p>囉唆 is a colloquial term for talkativeness.</p>
<p>繁縟 complains of overelaborate detail in description.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
    </div>
